Lockdowns are the last option - they have a devastating impact on the economy and millions of lives. 
We must first accelerate vaccination dramatically, curb superspreaders, enforce masks etc.  We should have been doing this for months.
Lockdowns come when these measures fail.

text: The tension and need for balance between Executive Power and Personal Liberty has occurred all through human history. Citizens often lack power, institutions can prove to be frail. Hence the Courts must hold the scales, and be the ultimate protector of individual freedom. (3/3)

name: Vikram Chandra
text: The State, not just in India but anywhere in the world, always tries to maximise its power. It's only natural. It is for citizens, for democratic institutions, and, above all, for the Courts to defend personal freedom and liberty. (2/3)
